    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin fries</p><p>Add the<strong> fries</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, your <strong>ground paprika </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp \u2013 these are your<strong> paprika fries</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-double-chicken-breast-burger-with-lettuce-and-fries/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>chicken </strong>to a bowl with your<strong> ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong>,<strong> garam masala </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-double-chicken-breast-burger-with-lettuce-and-fries/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-double-chicken-breast-burger-with-lettuce-and-fries/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>browned chicken</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and reserve the pan</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-14 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>spiced chicken</strong></p><p>(Doubled your protein? Do this in batches!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-double-chicken-breast-burger-with-lettuce-and-fries/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mango chutney </strong>and <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>mayo </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>mango mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-double-chicken-breast-burger-with-lettuce-and-fries/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the fries have been in the oven for an initial 20 min, move them to one side of the tray[s] and add your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> to the other side</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 4-5 min or until the ciabatta is hot and toasted</p><p>Carefully slice the <strong>toasted ciabatta</strong> in half before serving</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-double-chicken-breast-burger-with-lettuce-and-fries/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and shred finely</p><p>Add your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>to a bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and mix until dissolved</p><p>Stir in your <strong>curry powder </strong>and the <strong>remaining mayo</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>shredded lettuce </strong>to the bowl and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>curried lettuce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-double-chicken-breast-burger-with-lettuce-and-fries/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>toasted ciabatta base </strong>with a dollop of <strong>mango mayo</strong>, the <strong>spiced chicken</strong>, a handful of <strong>curried lettuce </strong>and the <strong>toasted ciabatta lid </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>Indian-style chicken burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>paprika fries</strong> and <strong>remaining curried lettuce</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
